1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:01,510
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,510 --> 00:00:03,310
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,380 --> 00:00:05,140
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:08,510 --> 00:00:10,120
Stay alert at all times.

5
00:00:10,650 --> 00:00:14,090
No one, and I mean no one,
is allowed to visit the chairman.

6
00:00:22,830 --> 00:00:24,430
Hello, this is Kim Myung Hui.

7
00:00:25,430 --> 00:00:28,630
We've identified the drug.

8
00:00:29,700 --> 00:00:30,700
There's a chance...

9
00:00:31,040 --> 00:00:34,370
we may be able to bring
Chairman Park around.

10
00:00:42,380 --> 00:00:43,650
As for the details,

11
00:00:44,280 --> 00:00:47,050
I've already spoken to your son.

12
00:00:47,490 --> 00:00:49,350
Okay, I understand.

13
00:00:50,320 --> 00:00:51,320
What was that?

14
00:00:53,360 --> 00:00:54,360
What was that call about?

15
00:00:55,760 --> 00:00:57,330
I'll check when I get to the office.

16
00:00:58,200 --> 00:01:00,700
- Sure.
- I asked what that call was about!

17
00:01:01,300 --> 00:01:03,100
Do I have to explain
every little thing to you?

18
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:05,700
It's work-related,
so mind your own business.

19
00:01:10,780 --> 00:01:12,480
Managing office work
in a situation like this?

20
00:01:15,480 --> 00:01:17,580
You. Tail Kim Myung Hui today.

21
00:01:17,850 --> 00:01:20,920
Watch her every move at the office
and report back to me.

22
00:01:21,220 --> 00:01:23,520
- Got it?
- Yes, understood.

23
00:01:32,530 --> 00:01:33,830
I heard from Mrs. Han.

24
00:01:34,330 --> 00:01:35,830
She found out what the drug was.

25
00:01:36,370 --> 00:01:39,840
Yes. It was a mix of a sedative
and an opioid painkiller.

26
00:01:40,510 --> 00:01:42,570
Is there a way to wake him up?

27
00:01:49,010 --> 00:01:51,180
She said this drug is the antidote.

28
00:01:51,380 --> 00:01:54,650
If we inject him with this,
he'll wake up right away?

29
00:01:54,990 --> 00:01:58,720
About that...
She said she can't be sure.

30
00:01:59,620 --> 00:02:01,030
She said we need to test it out.

31
00:02:01,330 --> 00:02:02,330
Test it out?

32
00:02:02,490 --> 00:02:05,700
If he responds to this drug,
it'll wake him up.

33
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:10,770
But if he doesn't,
any treatment will be useless.

34
00:02:12,170 --> 00:02:15,640
You mean he might never wake up?

35
00:02:18,710 --> 00:02:19,710
Yes.

36
00:02:20,480 --> 00:02:23,210
He'll remain unconscious like this
and eventually...

37
00:02:24,350 --> 00:02:25,380
pass away.

38
00:02:26,820 --> 00:02:29,120
Which means we'll have no way
to take down Oh Jung Ran.

39
00:02:30,220 --> 00:02:32,090
Let's not lose hope yet.

40
00:02:33,660 --> 00:02:34,660
You're right.

41
00:02:34,690 --> 00:02:37,800
To save Father, we first need to see
if he responds to this.

42
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:39,930
Okay. Let's find a way.

43
00:02:40,530 --> 00:02:42,970
Until then,
this stays just between us.

44
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:54,310
Please produce an exposé
with these materials.

45
00:02:55,610 --> 00:02:56,980
It'll cover...

46
00:02:57,450 --> 00:03:00,390
Chairman Park Tae Ho of Adele Group
and his alleged involvement...

47
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:02,590
in an illegal M and A deal...

48
00:03:02,890 --> 00:03:05,360
and a suspicious car accident
seven years ago.

49
00:03:06,390 --> 00:03:07,890
Chairman Park Tae Ho?

50
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:13,200
Don't be intimidated by Adele Group.

51
00:03:14,430 --> 00:03:15,670
Please, just reveal the truth.

52
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:18,400
I'll fund the production.

53
00:03:31,850 --> 00:03:33,350
What do you mean you won't do it?

54
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:36,090
The allegations are serious,
but there's no evidence,

55
00:03:36,420 --> 00:03:37,460
only suspicion.

56
00:03:38,260 --> 00:03:41,930
It's a stretch to name Chairman Park
of Adele Group as the culprit.

57
00:03:43,230 --> 00:03:46,560
To make this documentary,
I need hard evidence.

58
00:03:49,170 --> 00:03:50,170
Evidence?

59
00:03:54,270 --> 00:03:56,070
If a key whistleblower
were to come forward,

60
00:03:58,040 --> 00:03:59,040
what then?

61
00:04:00,350 --> 00:04:01,850
What if I,
Chairman Park Tae Ho's son...

62
00:04:04,380 --> 00:04:06,050
were to personally expose
my own father's crimes?

63
00:04:08,090 --> 00:04:11,390
Wouldn't a claim from Adele Group
carry more weight?

64
00:04:15,390 --> 00:04:17,800
Please reconsider.

65
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:20,900
You'd have to reveal your face
and your full identity.

66
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:22,800
Are you prepared to do that?

67
00:04:25,540 --> 00:04:26,540
Yes.

68
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:29,040
I'll do it.

69
00:04:31,210 --> 00:04:33,750
In that case,
I'll review the materials again...

70
00:04:34,910 --> 00:04:35,910
and get in touch.

71
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:37,880
Then...

72
00:04:48,060 --> 00:04:49,060
Hyun Jun.

73
00:04:49,630 --> 00:04:51,100
Are you really going
to do this yourself?

74
00:04:52,030 --> 00:04:53,360
Are you sure you'll be okay?

75
00:04:53,830 --> 00:04:55,730
By the time the documentary airs,

76
00:04:58,670 --> 00:05:00,510
I'll be the chairman of Adele.

77
00:05:00,910 --> 00:05:01,910
At that point,

78
00:05:02,840 --> 00:05:04,740
I'll reveal the truth...

79
00:05:06,210 --> 00:05:08,110
and make you the chairman of Adele.

80
00:05:09,450 --> 00:05:10,450
That way,

81
00:05:10,980 --> 00:05:13,820
everyone will know you're a victim
of the Temi Bio incident.

82
00:05:16,150 --> 00:05:17,260
Given your abilities,

83
00:05:18,390 --> 00:05:19,920
you'll have proven yourself...

84
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:21,660
through the exclusive
development rights project,

85
00:05:23,590 --> 00:05:26,030
which will help you gain the support
of many shareholders.

86
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:28,400
That's my plan,

87
00:05:32,070 --> 00:05:33,070
my apology to you,

88
00:05:37,110 --> 00:05:38,110
and proof of my love.

89
00:05:40,380 --> 00:05:41,380
But I...

90
00:05:43,210 --> 00:05:45,550
have nothing to give you.

91
00:05:46,020 --> 00:05:47,590
You've already given me everything.

92
00:05:50,690 --> 00:05:51,690
A place by your side.

93
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:07,340
(Receptor Antagonist Administration
Protocol and Prognosis...)

94
00:06:07,410 --> 00:06:09,740
(for ER Patients
With Impaired Consciousness)

95
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:15,010
Will this antidote even work
on Father?

96
00:06:16,850 --> 00:06:18,880
If he doesn't wake up,

97
00:06:21,650 --> 00:06:23,520
I don't think
I could ever forgive her.

98
00:06:27,890 --> 00:06:28,890
Min Jun.

99
00:06:32,060 --> 00:06:34,000
Min Jun, I got my job back.

100
00:06:35,630 --> 00:06:37,270
Right. That's good news.

101
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:43,170
What's wrong?
Are you worried about the chairman?

102
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:45,680
Yes, pretty much.

103
00:06:46,810 --> 00:06:49,750
It seems like something else
is bothering you, though.

104
00:06:51,450 --> 00:06:52,680
What is it? Talk to me.

105
00:06:53,220 --> 00:06:55,420
What's the problem? How can I help?

106
00:06:58,220 --> 00:07:01,660
You always seem to put me
before yourself.

107
00:07:03,260 --> 00:07:06,230
You're the most important person
to me.

108
00:07:07,570 --> 00:07:11,600
Then why are you hiding
the details of the accident?

109
00:07:12,370 --> 00:07:16,170
And why did Hyun Jun tell me
not to trust you...

110
00:07:17,180 --> 00:07:19,910
when you seem so devoted to me?

111
00:07:21,450 --> 00:07:25,080
I brought you something to celebrate
getting my job back.

112
00:07:27,520 --> 00:07:31,060
The snacks, supplements,
and juice you like.

113
00:07:31,790 --> 00:07:33,590
I got you all your favorite...

114
00:07:35,130 --> 00:07:36,230
things.

115
00:07:36,390 --> 00:07:37,900
(Head of Division 1, Park Min Jun)

116
00:07:39,260 --> 00:07:41,100
You're not wearing the watch
I gave you.

117
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,940
I wear mine all the time.

118
00:07:45,300 --> 00:07:46,640
Sorry about that.

119
00:07:47,310 --> 00:07:49,010
I've just been so out of it
because of my father.

120
00:07:49,270 --> 00:07:50,270
It's okay.

121
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:53,040
Then how about we go out for a bit?

122
00:07:53,540 --> 00:07:56,510
- What?
- Let's go for a walk.

123
00:08:15,870 --> 00:08:18,770
Are you two having an office date?

124
00:08:19,740 --> 00:08:22,810
His mother is the one
who put the chairman in a coma,

125
00:08:23,670 --> 00:08:26,440
yet they look completely carefree,
without a hint of guilt.

126
00:08:28,910 --> 00:08:32,080
All the while, my poor Min Jun is
worried sick about the chairman...

127
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,920
because of that certain someone.

128
00:08:42,590 --> 00:08:45,830
Hyun Jun was deeply hurt
by that incident, too.

129
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:47,600
That's why we're together.

130
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:49,800
After all,

131
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:54,170
we're getting married.

132
00:08:54,740 --> 00:08:57,840
Are you really going
to marry this woman?

133
00:08:58,510 --> 00:09:00,410
She tried to leak company secrets.

134
00:09:00,410 --> 00:09:01,510
That was...

135
00:09:01,650 --> 00:09:02,650
And as for you, Chloe,

136
00:09:03,380 --> 00:09:05,650
losing your memory
doesn't erase everything.

137
00:09:06,450 --> 00:09:09,420
Shouldn't you take a hard look
at what you've done?

138
00:09:10,590 --> 00:09:15,360
Besides, how can you marry someone
you don't even remember?

139
00:09:15,990 --> 00:09:17,630
You're one to talk, Mr. Park.

140
00:09:17,900 --> 00:09:20,670
You're with someone
you don't remember either.

141
00:09:28,270 --> 00:09:31,340
The issue with the company secrets
was all a misunderstanding.

142
00:09:31,340 --> 00:09:33,410
I heard it myself at the station.

143
00:09:33,710 --> 00:09:36,650
I confirmed that Father testified
in person.

144
00:09:36,710 --> 00:09:40,590
Father was going to apologize
to Chloe for that.

145
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:43,050
He was about to give us his blessing
to get married.

146
00:09:43,650 --> 00:09:44,820
I wonder about that.

147
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:47,930
The chairman
could've felt differently.

148
00:09:48,190 --> 00:09:49,690
But wait.

149
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:53,000
Thanks to your mother,

150
00:09:53,230 --> 00:09:55,600
we'll never know
what his true intentions were.

151
00:09:57,800 --> 00:09:58,800
I guess not.

152
00:09:59,570 --> 00:10:00,670
Oh, right.

153
00:10:00,970 --> 00:10:03,140
Why don't you tell us yourself,
Yu Na?

154
00:10:04,110 --> 00:10:06,610
The day Min Jun and Chloe
were run over,

155
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:10,510
you were there at the scene.

156
00:10:11,150 --> 00:10:12,250
She was?

157
00:10:13,050 --> 00:10:15,720
Since we're on the subject,
be honest.

158
00:10:16,190 --> 00:10:19,120
Do you have any proof
that I tried to leak...

159
00:10:20,220 --> 00:10:21,360
company secrets?

160
00:10:23,530 --> 00:10:24,530
That's...

161
00:10:29,730 --> 00:10:30,770
What's wrong?

162
00:10:31,700 --> 00:10:32,900
Cat got your tongue?

163
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:39,510
We'll leave you two...

164
00:10:40,680 --> 00:10:42,280
to talk about the rest on your own.

165
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:45,280
Let's go.

166
00:10:52,420 --> 00:10:54,290
Were you really there
when we were run over?

167
00:10:56,430 --> 00:10:58,330
- What?
- Let's be honest.

168
00:10:58,330 --> 00:11:00,460
You've been avoiding
talking about the accident.

169
00:11:00,930 --> 00:11:03,270
Is it because you didn't
want to admit you were there?

170
00:11:03,630 --> 00:11:07,410
Why?
What were you doing there that day?

171
00:11:08,310 --> 00:11:09,610
No, more importantly...

172
00:11:09,970 --> 00:11:13,310
Why were Chloe and I run over together
in the first place?

173
00:11:16,110 --> 00:11:18,320
I don't really know the details.

174
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:22,020
I was there for work
and saw it happen. That's all.

175
00:11:23,390 --> 00:11:27,560
Let's drop this conversation
and get out of here.

176
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:36,030
Let's take that walk
some other time.

177
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:38,770
I'm going to head in.

178
00:11:40,170 --> 00:11:41,470
Park Min Jun!

179
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:48,680
How could I ever tell him
what happened that day?

180
00:11:56,190 --> 00:11:57,520
Kim Myung Hui.

181
00:11:58,260 --> 00:12:00,520
She didn't try anything funny
at the office?

182
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:04,030
That's right.
She only met with Park Min Jun...

183
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:05,800
and stuck to her routine tasks.

184
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:10,970
It seems they're planning
to split the company like you said,

185
00:12:11,170 --> 00:12:13,700
so try to relax and get some rest.

186
00:12:13,870 --> 00:12:17,070
Relax? You know how ruthless
Kim Myung Hui can be.

187
00:12:17,140 --> 00:12:19,910
Even as president, what can she do
without Chairman Park?

188
00:12:20,710 --> 00:12:22,680
You've already put him
out of commission,

189
00:12:23,110 --> 00:12:25,120
so why are you still so on edge?

190
00:12:25,550 --> 00:12:27,150
If you keep this up,

191
00:12:27,220 --> 00:12:28,990
you're going to wear yourself out.

192
00:12:29,450 --> 00:12:30,550
If you're that worried,

193
00:12:30,550 --> 00:12:32,660
focus on your job and keep
a close eye on Park Tae Ho.

194
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:35,790
If you doze off and Kim Myung Hui
slips in again like last night,

195
00:12:35,830 --> 00:12:37,130
I'll kill you with my own two hands.

196
00:12:37,390 --> 00:12:38,830
Got it.

197
00:12:40,230 --> 00:12:42,170
Don't worry,
I'll keep a close watch.

198
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:54,040
Tonight?

199
00:12:54,380 --> 00:12:58,150
Yes. We need to test the antidote
before it's too late.

200
00:12:58,220 --> 00:13:01,490
Guards are right outside the door.
How are you planning to do it?

201
00:13:01,550 --> 00:13:03,490
Secretary Jung is waiting outside.

202
00:13:03,790 --> 00:13:06,690
With your help, I think I can get
into the master bedroom.

203
00:13:08,590 --> 00:13:10,330
What do you need me to do?

204
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:22,210
Make sure you guard him properly.

205
00:13:22,210 --> 00:13:24,210
I told you, I got it.

206
00:13:38,920 --> 00:13:39,920
What the...

207
00:13:40,490 --> 00:13:41,530
Did the power go out?

208
00:13:43,530 --> 00:13:46,260
You two, stay at your posts. Got it?

209
00:13:46,660 --> 00:13:48,970
I'll go check on the power.

210
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:53,400
Why would the power go out?

211
00:13:54,570 --> 00:13:55,710
Where...

212
00:14:04,420 --> 00:14:05,750
What's that noise?

213
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:09,090
I can hear Father in his room.
We should hurry in there.

214
00:14:10,690 --> 00:14:13,590
Get out of the way.
Can't you hear him groaning?

215
00:14:14,060 --> 00:14:15,330
This is an emergency.

216
00:14:15,330 --> 00:14:17,600
He almost died
of respiratory distress last time.

217
00:14:17,730 --> 00:14:18,900
Now get out of the way!

218
00:14:19,230 --> 00:14:22,430
If something happens to my father,
will you take full responsibility?

219
00:14:35,110 --> 00:14:36,110
What's going on?

220
00:14:36,780 --> 00:14:37,780
What is it?

221
00:14:38,580 --> 00:14:40,080
Nothing happened, did it?

222
00:14:53,130 --> 00:14:54,130
What is this?

223
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:56,900
Open this door. What's going on?

224
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:58,270
Open the door right now.

225
00:14:58,870 --> 00:15:02,710
You, open this door.
I said open the door!

226
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:06,340
I told you to guard him properly!

227
00:15:07,180 --> 00:15:08,610
Kim Myung Hui's in there, isn't she?

228
00:15:10,650 --> 00:15:12,380
You two are up to something again.

229
00:15:12,450 --> 00:15:15,390
It looked like an emergency,
so she went in to check on him.

230
00:15:15,450 --> 00:15:18,820
An emergency, my foot. Unbelievable.

231
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:22,360
Don't just stand there.
Open the door!

232
00:15:25,830 --> 00:15:28,700
What were you doing in there
with the door locked?

233
00:15:28,770 --> 00:15:32,900
The power suddenly went out,
so I went to check on the chairman.

234
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:36,940
I guess the door locked behind me
when I rushed in.

235
00:16:02,930 --> 00:16:06,140
Are you sure
you didn't do anything to him?

236
00:16:15,550 --> 00:16:16,610
Sir!

237
00:16:17,050 --> 00:16:18,050
Father!

238
00:16:20,380 --> 00:16:21,420
Oh...

239
00:16:21,950 --> 00:16:23,820
Oh Jung Ran...

240
00:16:27,460 --> 00:16:28,760
How dare...

241
00:16:29,730 --> 00:16:31,600
How dare you...

242
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:35,330
No. You can't wake up!

243
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:43,410
- Sir!
- Father!

244
00:17:01,660 --> 00:17:02,930
Father...

245
00:17:03,490 --> 00:17:05,130
reacted to the antidote.

246
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:08,200
That's right.
He woke up, if only for a moment.

247
00:17:08,770 --> 00:17:11,300
If we start treatment now,
we can wake him up.

248
00:17:11,970 --> 00:17:14,610
We need to get him out of here
and to the hospital immediately.

249
00:17:15,510 --> 00:17:19,240
To work behind Oh Jung Ran's back,
we need to be prepared.

250
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:22,580
We need a plan
that's both safe and foolproof.

251
00:17:29,290 --> 00:17:31,560
Mr. Shin is a star producer,

252
00:17:31,990 --> 00:17:36,290
and Park Hyun Jun is willing
to expose his own father's crimes.

253
00:17:37,560 --> 00:17:39,060
If we can get
the documentary produced,

254
00:17:39,060 --> 00:17:41,370
the public will definitely
take notice.

255
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:47,440
The police won't be able to ignore
the pressure for a reinvestigation.

256
00:17:47,910 --> 00:17:50,070
If Mr. Shin agrees to produce it,

257
00:17:50,270 --> 00:17:52,440
we'll have to keep things
very quiet.

258
00:17:53,040 --> 00:17:54,950
Even with Chairman Park unconscious,

259
00:17:54,950 --> 00:17:57,150
if Ms. Oh or President Kim
finds out,

260
00:17:57,210 --> 00:17:58,580
they might try to interfere.

261
00:17:59,120 --> 00:18:00,120
Right.

262
00:18:00,580 --> 00:18:03,320
This would be a devastating blow
to the Adele Group.

263
00:18:04,320 --> 00:18:05,320
And...

264
00:18:10,690 --> 00:18:13,600
I think
I need to speed up the wedding.

265
00:18:14,570 --> 00:18:15,700
The wedding too?

266
00:18:16,230 --> 00:18:19,900
I have to seize this opportunity
while Chairman Park Tae Ho is down.

267
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:24,040
I can join the Adele family
without the chairman interfering...

268
00:18:24,370 --> 00:18:27,580
and use Oh Jung Ran to get ahead
in the succession battle.

269
00:18:28,750 --> 00:18:31,150
I can expose the accident
from seven years ago...

270
00:18:31,150 --> 00:18:33,080
and demand a reinvestigation.

271
00:18:34,720 --> 00:18:38,560
I need to start putting my plans
into action as quickly as possible.

272
00:18:38,760 --> 00:18:41,830
It's still marriage, though.
Are you sure you'll be okay?

273
00:18:42,930 --> 00:18:45,600
Park Min Jun is still struggling
with his memory.

274
00:18:47,530 --> 00:18:48,730
Min Jun...

275
00:18:49,430 --> 00:18:51,540
Just the fact
that he saved my life...

276
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:53,300
is more than enough for me.

277
00:18:54,710 --> 00:18:57,670
I don't want to involve him
in my revenge...

278
00:18:58,580 --> 00:19:00,110
and risk him getting hurt again.

279
00:19:01,510 --> 00:19:04,010
Park Hyun Jun is the one I'll marry.

280
00:19:15,090 --> 00:19:16,430
What brings you here at this hour?

281
00:19:17,230 --> 00:19:19,700
Did something happen to my father?

282
00:19:21,430 --> 00:19:22,430
Well...

283
00:19:45,420 --> 00:19:48,290
Come on. Stop that.

284
00:19:48,890 --> 00:19:50,690
You gave him another dose,

285
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:53,760
and he's not even moving.

286
00:19:53,830 --> 00:19:55,370
Park Tae Ho opened his eyes...

287
00:19:55,900 --> 00:19:57,430
and looked right at me.

288
00:19:58,140 --> 00:20:00,640
I swear, he looked like
he wanted to kill me.

289
00:20:05,610 --> 00:20:07,180
I heard Father woke up.

290
00:20:07,880 --> 00:20:09,810
What? Who said he woke up?

291
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:13,180
It was just for a moment.
A very brief moment.

292
00:20:15,250 --> 00:20:19,760
I think the dose was too weak.
We need something stronger.

293
00:20:19,820 --> 00:20:21,020
We can't do that.

294
00:20:22,060 --> 00:20:23,960
If the chairman were to die,

295
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:25,830
the power of attorney
becomes invalid.

296
00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:28,100
The succession process
will begin immediately,

297
00:20:28,900 --> 00:20:31,940
giving Kim Myung Hui
and Park Min Jun legal rights.

298
00:20:32,570 --> 00:20:35,870
Right.
Kim Myung Hui and Park Min Jun.

299
00:20:36,410 --> 00:20:38,880
They did something for sure.

300
00:20:39,510 --> 00:20:41,240
What are you talking about?

301
00:20:44,080 --> 00:20:45,080
That's it.

302
00:20:45,520 --> 00:20:47,820
I can't just stand around
guarding Park Tae Ho.

303
00:20:48,090 --> 00:20:50,820
Before Kim Myung Hui
and Park Min Jun get in the way,

304
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:52,760
I have to act fast.

305
00:20:54,660 --> 00:20:57,090
So what's your decision?

306
00:20:57,090 --> 00:20:59,700
Are you just going to sit there
feeling ashamed and angry?

307
00:21:00,060 --> 00:21:03,430
Or are you going to help me
take over Adele?

308
00:21:15,780 --> 00:21:16,850
Yu Na.

309
00:21:17,610 --> 00:21:19,820
Why the long face?

310
00:21:20,380 --> 00:21:24,350
Just yesterday, you were so thrilled
about getting your job back.

311
00:21:24,760 --> 00:21:27,720
So why are you moping around
like this today?

312
00:21:28,260 --> 00:21:30,790
Why? Did you return to work...

313
00:21:31,230 --> 00:21:34,460
and find the company in chaos
after Chairman Park collapsed?

314
00:21:34,530 --> 00:21:35,970
It's not that.

315
00:21:39,440 --> 00:21:41,200
I can't predict
how Min Jun really feels.

316
00:21:41,970 --> 00:21:45,780
One moment he's sweet to me,
and the next, he's distant.

317
00:21:46,540 --> 00:21:49,310
I'm afraid he'll change
when his memory...

318
00:21:50,380 --> 00:21:51,650
comes back.

319
00:21:51,850 --> 00:21:53,680
For crying out loud.

320
00:21:54,080 --> 00:21:57,490
Look, if you're going to be
in a relationship,

321
00:21:57,550 --> 00:21:59,820
you're supposed to be happy.

322
00:21:59,820 --> 00:22:02,090
If you keep moping around
feeling anxious,

323
00:22:02,230 --> 00:22:04,260
how long do you think
you can keep this up?

324
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:07,760
Don't even suggest
I break up with him.

325
00:22:07,830 --> 00:22:11,230
Please. Like you'd actually do it...

326
00:22:11,300 --> 00:22:13,470
if I told you to.

327
00:22:13,940 --> 00:22:18,640
Instead of trembling in fear,
use this chance to lock him down.

328
00:22:19,140 --> 00:22:21,950
You're his girlfriend,
and you've got your job back.

329
00:22:22,010 --> 00:22:24,350
The only thing left is marriage.

330
00:22:24,750 --> 00:22:25,750
Marriage?

331
00:22:26,620 --> 00:22:28,590
Now of all times, when
Chairman Park has just collapsed?

332
00:22:28,620 --> 00:22:30,350
Oh, please.

333
00:22:30,520 --> 00:22:31,920
Even in the middle of a war,

334
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:35,630
people fall in love
and have children.

335
00:22:35,630 --> 00:22:37,260
Anyway,

336
00:22:37,490 --> 00:22:39,260
once you've gone through
with the marriage,

337
00:22:39,260 --> 00:22:42,570
what can Min Jun do
even if he gets his memory back?

338
00:22:42,900 --> 00:22:44,900
And how am I supposed
to get married?

339
00:22:46,140 --> 00:22:48,610
If you're going to say that,
why don't you actually help?

340
00:22:49,010 --> 00:22:51,270
Go see Park Min Jun
and President Kim Myung Hui...

341
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:54,210
and pressure them
to let us get married.

342
00:22:55,050 --> 00:22:58,320
- Us?
- What? Pressure them?

343
00:22:59,480 --> 00:23:00,950
Okay, sure.

344
00:23:02,250 --> 00:23:05,420
I mean, that's my specialty.

345
00:23:06,920 --> 00:23:08,060
Don't you worry.

346
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:20,800
Promise me that Father
will be the last one.

347
00:23:22,770 --> 00:23:25,040
Hurting people
while claiming it's for my sake?

348
00:23:28,250 --> 00:23:29,450
That has to stop now.

349
00:23:31,250 --> 00:23:32,350
Let's be honest.

350
00:23:33,150 --> 00:23:35,290
You're not going to give them
half of Adele.

351
00:23:35,290 --> 00:23:37,020
Your greed won't allow it, Mom.

352
00:23:37,620 --> 00:23:41,420
You can wait for the right moment
to force them out,

353
00:23:42,930 --> 00:23:44,930
but you are not to hurt them.

354
00:23:45,700 --> 00:23:47,000
Promise me that,

355
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:52,270
and I'll be the greedy snob...

356
00:23:53,300 --> 00:23:54,940
who wants Adele.

357
00:23:55,240 --> 00:23:59,040
Kim Myung Hui and Park Min Jun.
You don't have to worry about them.

358
00:24:01,180 --> 00:24:03,110
Until I can
get rid of them for good,

359
00:24:03,450 --> 00:24:05,280
I'll let them live for now.

360
00:24:18,530 --> 00:24:21,360
The president's office is this way,

361
00:24:21,900 --> 00:24:23,730
and the director's office
is that way.

362
00:24:24,730 --> 00:24:26,070
Which one should we hit first?

363
00:24:26,540 --> 00:24:27,540
Good question.

364
00:24:30,610 --> 00:24:31,610
Okay.

365
00:24:38,180 --> 00:24:39,280
What now?

366
00:24:42,690 --> 00:24:43,690
What is it?

367
00:24:46,790 --> 00:24:48,060
She's coming this way!

368
00:24:48,120 --> 00:24:51,490
No need to be scared.
Isn't that Clyde?

369
00:24:51,930 --> 00:24:53,230
I'm sorry,

370
00:24:54,260 --> 00:24:55,500
but do you know me?

371
00:24:55,670 --> 00:24:58,670
What ridiculous nonsense is this?

372
00:24:58,940 --> 00:25:00,440
Do we know you?

373
00:25:00,740 --> 00:25:03,210
It's just that you both look
so familiar.

374
00:25:03,510 --> 00:25:04,510
Especially...

375
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:08,580
- him.
- Why are you doing this to me?

376
00:25:08,880 --> 00:25:13,120
I don't know anything. I don't!

377
00:25:14,220 --> 00:25:15,690
My goodness, what is this?

378
00:25:15,690 --> 00:25:17,550
Take a good look at my face.

379
00:25:19,060 --> 00:25:20,760
You really don't recognize me?

380
00:25:21,630 --> 00:25:22,630
Jin...

381
00:25:25,630 --> 00:25:28,700
Goodness me. Honey! My gosh.

382
00:25:28,700 --> 00:25:29,730
Dad!

383
00:25:31,300 --> 00:25:32,700
It's all right.

384
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:34,910
What is this?

385
00:25:36,640 --> 00:25:37,640
What exactly did I do?

386
00:25:38,510 --> 00:25:42,110
They looked familiar,
so I asked if they knew me.

387
00:25:43,910 --> 00:25:46,020
Why are you so frightened?

388
00:25:46,750 --> 00:25:48,920
You're acting like
you did something wrong.

389
00:25:49,020 --> 00:25:50,990
Wait. What?

390
00:25:51,320 --> 00:25:55,030
What in the world
are you babbling about?

391
00:25:55,560 --> 00:25:56,830
If not, then whatever.

392
00:25:57,930 --> 00:26:01,460
I have to go see Hyun Jun,
so I'll be on my way.

393
00:26:02,670 --> 00:26:06,540
That little witch. I swear...

394
00:26:07,770 --> 00:26:08,770
Goodness.

395
00:26:09,840 --> 00:26:14,610
Come on. Let's get you up. Honestly.

396
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:29,660
The reason we're here is...

397
00:26:29,960 --> 00:26:32,000
You see,

398
00:26:32,460 --> 00:26:36,370
we need to know how long
you're going to make...

399
00:26:36,430 --> 00:26:38,400
our Yu Na wait.

400
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:40,370
Even if you've lost your memory,

401
00:26:40,670 --> 00:26:44,210
you still have to tell us
if you plan to marry her.

402
00:26:45,510 --> 00:26:49,010
Mom, I told you not to push
the marriage issue.

403
00:26:50,650 --> 00:26:53,750
Yes, I'll take my time to think
about the marriage.

404
00:26:54,720 --> 00:26:58,050
I'm sorry,
but I have a meeting soon.

405
00:26:58,120 --> 00:27:00,420
Right. Of course.

406
00:27:00,490 --> 00:27:03,790
Take your time, my son-in-law.

407
00:27:07,700 --> 00:27:08,700
Right.

408
00:27:10,100 --> 00:27:12,600
By the way, do you know Chloe well?

409
00:27:12,840 --> 00:27:13,840
What?

410
00:27:14,640 --> 00:27:16,470
Chloe?

411
00:27:17,640 --> 00:27:20,080
I was passing by earlier,
and I noticed that the two of you...

412
00:27:20,540 --> 00:27:23,010
looked frightened
when you saw Chloe.

413
00:27:23,080 --> 00:27:26,080
What do you mean
we were scared of her?

414
00:27:26,180 --> 00:27:29,190
It's just that she looks so much
like the late Baek Jin Ju.

415
00:27:29,190 --> 00:27:30,220
Dad!

416
00:27:31,820 --> 00:27:35,090
Why bring up someone
who's nothing but trouble?

417
00:27:37,260 --> 00:27:40,460
Don't you have a meeting soon?
I'll see my parents out myself.

418
00:27:41,360 --> 00:27:42,370
Sure.

419
00:27:42,900 --> 00:27:45,340
We'll get going now.

420
00:27:46,270 --> 00:27:47,270
Right.

421
00:27:50,210 --> 00:27:52,080
- We'll see you next time.
- Sure.

422
00:28:02,820 --> 00:28:04,050
Baek Jin Ju?

423
00:28:13,660 --> 00:28:15,400
To get Chairman Park out,

424
00:28:15,770 --> 00:28:17,930
we have to get past
Oh Jung Ran's security.

425
00:28:18,030 --> 00:28:20,200
Finding an opportunity
won't be easy.

426
00:28:20,970 --> 00:28:22,970
We'll have to find one
any way we can.

427
00:28:27,540 --> 00:28:29,310
You need to go
to the chairman's office.

428
00:28:29,880 --> 00:28:32,920
- Oh Jung Ran made a move.
- What? Really?

429
00:28:38,150 --> 00:28:40,620
Is it true you've disbanded
the Emergency Management Team?

430
00:28:42,130 --> 00:28:44,190
I already have
the chairman's full authority,

431
00:28:44,830 --> 00:28:47,600
so why do we need
an Emergency Management Team...

432
00:28:48,060 --> 00:28:49,400
or special management rights?

433
00:28:49,400 --> 00:28:51,840
But we agreed to split Adele.

434
00:28:52,340 --> 00:28:55,110
Then the management rights
should also be split...

435
00:28:55,440 --> 00:28:57,370
between us fairly.

436
00:28:58,810 --> 00:29:00,610
Let's be clear about the deal.

437
00:29:01,310 --> 00:29:03,480
You two only agreed
to split the company.

438
00:29:03,480 --> 00:29:05,080
The issue of management rights...

439
00:29:05,720 --> 00:29:07,520
is a completely separate matter.

440
00:29:08,220 --> 00:29:09,720
I'd like to add something.

441
00:29:10,150 --> 00:29:12,960
A short while ago, Adele Group
and JKL Partners agreed to form...

442
00:29:13,720 --> 00:29:16,830
a joint venture for exclusive rights
to overseas resources.

443
00:29:18,330 --> 00:29:19,430
First you took
the management rights,

444
00:29:20,130 --> 00:29:22,500
and now you've taken
the exclusive development deal too?

445
00:29:23,670 --> 00:29:26,700
I also intend to fast-track
the approved wedding.

446
00:29:30,070 --> 00:29:31,610
For someone with no memory,

447
00:29:32,040 --> 00:29:34,340
you're certainly quick to lock down
business deals and a wedding.

448
00:29:36,480 --> 00:29:39,880
I'm simply moving forward
with what was already arranged.

449
00:29:40,620 --> 00:29:41,950
Given the circumstances,

450
00:29:43,290 --> 00:29:44,520
I'm just
speeding things up a little.

451
00:29:47,820 --> 00:29:51,090
Mother, when do you think would be
a good time for our wedding?

452
00:29:51,490 --> 00:29:53,530
Considering the impact it'll have
on our joint venture,

453
00:29:53,530 --> 00:29:55,400
isn't it a case
of the sooner, the better?

454
00:29:56,630 --> 00:29:57,630
Well,

455
00:29:58,770 --> 00:30:00,000
if we are to hold a wedding...

456
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:01,840
I can't approve of this marriage.

457
00:30:04,370 --> 00:30:07,580
I don't believe that's any
of your business, Ms. Kim.

458
00:30:08,610 --> 00:30:09,610
He's right.

459
00:30:11,410 --> 00:30:13,750
Who do you think you are,
meddling in my son's marriage?

460
00:30:13,880 --> 00:30:17,290
The joint venture hinges
on this marriage,

461
00:30:17,550 --> 00:30:19,390
and it will affect
the succession issue.

462
00:30:20,060 --> 00:30:23,430
Splitting the Adele Group in half
must come before the wedding.

463
00:30:24,830 --> 00:30:26,430
Forget what you think
the proper order is.

464
00:30:27,160 --> 00:30:30,800
Don't get cocky just because
we made a deal. Get over yourself.

465
00:30:31,170 --> 00:30:33,000
My son's wedding is
my decision to make.

466
00:30:33,100 --> 00:30:36,040
They were getting married anyway.
I'll just move the wedding up.

467
00:30:36,870 --> 00:30:41,480
You know what?
Have the ceremony this weekend.

468
00:30:43,510 --> 00:30:44,510
Mom?

469
00:30:50,620 --> 00:30:51,620
What just happened?

470
00:30:51,890 --> 00:30:53,420
Was she trying to stop the wedding,

471
00:30:53,420 --> 00:30:54,720
or was she provoking Oh Jung Ran
into rushing things?

472
00:30:56,730 --> 00:30:58,330
I knew trying to stop the wedding...

473
00:30:58,330 --> 00:30:59,930
would only make Oh Jung Ran
move it up.

474
00:31:00,830 --> 00:31:02,330
On your son's wedding day,

475
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:04,930
the house will be empty.

476
00:31:05,840 --> 00:31:08,040
That's when
I'll wake up Chairman Park.

477
00:31:15,810 --> 00:31:16,880
Baek Jin Ju.

478
00:31:17,650 --> 00:31:20,420
I've never heard that name before,
so why...

479
00:31:25,890 --> 00:31:26,960
Why on earth...

480
00:31:34,430 --> 00:31:36,430
- Here.
- Happy birthday to you too,

481
00:31:36,430 --> 00:31:37,430
Baek Jin Ju.

482
00:31:51,450 --> 00:31:52,880
Happy birthday, Min Jun.

483
00:31:54,220 --> 00:31:56,450
Happy birthday to you too,
Baek Jin Ju.

484
00:32:40,730 --> 00:32:43,730
(Pearl in Red)

485
00:32:44,170 --> 00:32:46,470
What's the truth
and what are the lies?

486
00:32:46,770 --> 00:32:49,110
Baek Jin Ju, Chloe...
What's going on?

487
00:32:49,540 --> 00:32:52,210
Is he starting to remember Jin Ju
and everything about her?

488
00:32:52,980 --> 00:32:55,780
What do I do?
I can't let him regain his memories.

489
00:32:56,110 --> 00:32:57,450
This marriage is the first step...

490
00:32:57,450 --> 00:33:00,620
toward gaining the influence
and power I need to become chairman.

491
00:33:00,820 --> 00:33:03,220
I love you, Baek Jin Ju.

492
00:33:06,860 --> 00:33:08,860
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
